record.title: TEMPORARY TAX RELIEF ACT OF 2007--MOTION TO PROCEED
record.narrative:
TEMPORARY TAX RELIEF ACT OF 2007--MOTION TO PROCEED -- (Senate - December 05, 2007)

[Page: S14774]
record.chair: Under the previous order, the Senate will resume consideration of the motion to proceed to H.R. 3996, which the clerk will report.
The assistant legislative clerk read as follows:
A motion to proceed to the bill (H.R. 3996) to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to extend certain expiring provisions, and for other purposes.

speaking.paragraph: Madam President, it is my understanding there is a motion to proceed that is now before the Senate. I ask to withdraw it.

record.chair: Without objection, the motion is withdrawn.

speaking.paragraph: What now is the pending business?
